[Your Company] + [Partner Company]
## The Opportunity
## Partnership Vision (Shared Goals, Value for each party)
## Proposed Structure (Type, Roles & Responsibilities table, Revenue Sharing)
## Pilot Program (Phase, Evaluation Criteria)
## Next Steps""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "KPIs",
        "Partner Company",
        "Partnership Type",
        "Pilot Duration",
        "Revenue Sharing",
        "Roles",
        "Shared Goals",
        "Your Company" .

oc:kn_2dbee84d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always, before generating any proposal" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Cannot research the specific client automatically — user must provide context. Pricing must be provided by the user. Legal terms should be reviewed by counsel." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The skill generates structure and persuasive content but cannot fabricate client intelligence or legal terms" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_3919ffd2 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating a full sales/service proposal" ;
    oc:directiveContent """# [Proposal Title]

## Executive Summary
[2-3 paragraph overview + key highlights]

## Understanding Your Needs
### Current Situation / Goals & Objectives / Key Requirements

## Proposed Solution
### Overview / Deliverables table / Approach & Methodology

## Investment
### Pricing Options (multiple) / Payment Terms / Inclusions / Exclusions

## Timeline
[Phase table with duration, start, end]

## Why [Your Company]
### Experience / Case Studies / Team

## Next Steps
[Numbered action items]

## Terms & Conditions

## Contact""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Client Company",
        "Date",
        "Deliverables",
        "Pricing",
        "Proposal Title",
        "Team",
        "Timeline",
        "Valid until",
        "Your Company" .

oc:kn_428aabb8 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring the pricing/investment section" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Offer multiple pricing options when possible, anchor with the higher option first, be transparent about inclusions/exclusions, and justify the investment." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Multiple options give clients perceived control; anchoring high makes the recommended option look reasonable" .

oc:kn_801afc5c a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the proposed solution section" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Focus on outcomes not activities in the solution section. Explain WHY the approach works, not just WHAT will be done." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Clients buy outcomes and value, not task lists" .

oc:kn_bd81ebab a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the client needs understanding section" ;
    oc:directiveContent "In the Understanding section, reference specific client challenges, use their language and terminology, and acknowledge their goals explicitly" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Demonstrating deep client understanding builds trust and differentiates from generic proposals" .

oc:kn_d5748546 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When closing any proposal" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never create a proposal without a clear call to action. Next steps must be crystal clear, friction-free (easy to say yes), and include appropriate urgency." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Ambiguous next steps cause delays and lost deals — the CTA is the most critical conversion element" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_de5f4fc0 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating a quick quote proposal" ;
    oc:directiveContent """# Quote for [Service/Product]
To/From/Date/Quote #/Valid for
## Scope of Work
## Pricing [Item | Qty | Unit Price | Total table]
## Timeline
## Terms
## To Accept [signature line]""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Client Name",
        "Items",
        "Pricing",
        "Quote Number",
        "Service/Product" .

oc:kn_fe8c83ab a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any proposal executive summary" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Write the Executive Summary last, after completing the full proposal. It must stand alone and lead with client benefits, not features. Keep it to 1 page maximum." ;
    oc:hasRationale "An executive summary that reads independently can circulate among decision-makers without the full proposal" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

